Wash and dry produce. Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}(minced). Halve, core, and thinly slice @green bell pepper{1}(thinly sliced into strips).

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1/2%tablespoon} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add garlic; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @water{1%cup} and @salt{1/4%tsp}. Bring to a boil, then add @white quinoa{1/2%cup}; cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until quinoa is tender and water has evaporated, ~{15-20%minutes}. TIP: Drain any excess water if necessary.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While quinoa cooks, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and cut crosswise into ½-inch-thick strips.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1/2%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer chicken to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1/2%tablespoon} in pan used for chicken over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper and @shredded red cabbage{4%ounce}; cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon}, half the @Szechuan paste{2%tablespoon}, half the @cornstarch{1%tablespoon}, @water{1/3%cup}, and @sugar{1%tsp} to pan with veggies. Stir to combine.

> For 4 servings, use all the Szechuan paste, all the cornstarch, ½ cup water, and 2 tsp sugar.

Add chicken and simmer, stirring occasionally, until sauce is slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Fluff quinoa with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon}.

Divide quinoa between #bowls{} and top with chicken and veggie stir-fry. Spoon any remaining sauce from pan on top and serve.